The party began with the minister's welcoming words and the dinner was followed by a dance evening on live music.
Answer to [origo]'s question: Evening dress was not mandatory at all at this ball.
The Ministries of Health, Labour and Local Government are preparing a sober party.
The Ministry of Health will organize a show and a party for its employees, in its walls, for 400,000 forints.
On the other hand, Mónika Lamperth, Minister of Labour, does not invite his employees officially to a Christmas party but to a working meeting at the end of the year.
One hundred and eighty people are expected to be invited to have coffee and to eat donuts, communicated the press service, the party will cost only 350,000 forints.
Gordon Bajnai, Minister of Local Government, will simply invite his collaborators to have a drink in the aula of the Ministry of Local Government and Territorial Planning.
The Ministry of Finance (PM) will organize a Christmas party in its large hall, at which 436 employees are expected.
He plans to spend 2,500 forints per guest including a buffet and a drink.
Since the arrival of János Veres, PM employees celebrate Christmas each year in the same way.
No festive atmosphere is planned, the official character is reinforced not only by the minister's presentation but also by the holiday time taking place in the afternoon.
The Ministry of Agriculture will host a reception on 20 January to celebrate the New Year, the Christmas party will not take place.
The reception will be held at Vajdahunyad Castle, located in the town wood, and according to the Ministry's communication, 1,000 forints per person are calculated for the hundred guests.
According to the press service, this is going to be a very simple cocktail to which only foreign diplomats accredited in Hungary will be invited.
These cocktails, organized every year, are started with a few words of welcome from the minister followed by a modest meal.
The Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Ministry of Education and Culture do not celebrate at all for Christmas, have communicated to [origo] the respective press services.
The press service of the Ministry of the Environment did not know the price of the official Christmas party.
However, more than four hundred people were invited to the festival at the Museum of Decorative Art.
The forces of the mega strike gather together
The unions of the League and the National Association of Workers' Councils will set up, on Friday, their strike commission, which will be responsible for coordinating the strike on Monday.
On Saturday, a general protest assembly will be held and on Monday, the day of the final vote on the Health Care Fund Act, the strike will begin.
This action will certainly cause important traffic jams because rail traffic will be stopped almost completely and employees of BKV (common transport company) will also strike until 1 p.m.
The Unions de la Ligue will announce, Friday afternoon, the details of their Monday strike, organized with the National Association of Workers' Councils.
The strike committee of LIGA - MOSZ will also be set up and will serve as coordinator of Monday's actions.
On Saturday, a general protest assembly will be held and, starting on Monday, organizations joining the strike will stop work for an indefinite period of time if they fail to reach an agreement with the government.
This means that the date of the end of the strike, starting from the day of the vote in parliament on the law on health funds, is not defined.
If the National Assembly does not adopt the Health Fund Act, the unions will immediately withdraw the call for strike action.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide on the next steps.
According to the Monday agenda of the National Assembly, it is likely that the vote on the Health Care Fund Act will take place only late in the evening or at night.
Due to the strike scheduled for Monday, major traffic jams are foreseen: the railways will stop work for an indefinite period and during the morning part of the public transport in Budapest and more than half of the Volán companies are at risk of being stopped.
At the same time, at different points in the country, half of the way will also be blocked.
Many trade unions and civil organizations have joined the call to strike, the list of them is constantly updated on the Ligue website.
Some organizations report an indefinite strike, others report a temporary stoppage of work.
Until Thursday afternoon the MÁV (Hungarian Railway Chemins) and the Free Trade Union of Railways (VDSZSZ) have failed to reach an agreement on minimum services, but as Christmas holidays approach, more and more people are taking the train.
According to current communications, public transport in Budapest will strike from the beginning of service until 1 p.m., the Budapest airport between 7 a.m. and 9 a.m., the Industrial Unions of Electricity and Thermal Energy of the League will strike for four hours, the Teachers' Union and the Democratic Union of Teachers have called to strike for two hours and from 2 a.m. to 8 a.m. respectively.
The National Association of Physicians will strike across the country in alternation, the Health and Social Workers' Union (EDDSZ) attached to the SZEF will carry out a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands, formulated by the League, demands that the government withdraw its proposal for health reform and submit a new concept to social debate.
The second claim requires that the new retirement calculation method to be introduced from next year be introduced in several stages.
The third claim seeks a guarantee, with regard to retirement before the legal age, that would allow the functions that deserve it to be transferred into the system before 2010.
The fourth reason for the action is the rejection by the Free Trade Union of Railways (VDSZSZ), attached to the Unions of the League, of the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport concerning the secondary railway lines and the waiting for another proposal.
Political Capital: Hungarian Guard increased risk country
According to the Risk Analysis Division of the Political Capital (Risk Analysis Division), the activities of the Hungarian Guard, formed last August, with the support of the Jobbik Magyarországért Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary) increase, in several respects, the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In its "risk warning", society points out that, in connection with the work of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that "in the short term aggressive ethnic clashes can occur as a result of the growing ethnic tension already existing between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy population of Hungary".
The research institute added that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy to probably provoke this situation is the main reason for this.
As they say, this is due to one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: "public actors have passed the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of radical and extreme political groupings which have based a political strategy on the dispute between the Gypsies and Hungarians".
The problem is aggravated, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are strengthened and the arrival of aggressive conflicts is more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, as a result of the increased attention of the Hungarian and international media, the Hungarian Guard's activity "has significantly deteriorated Hungary's image abroad, particularly with regard to confidence in the stability and democratic maturity of the country".
They recall that, following greater publicity given to the reorganization of the radical and extreme right-wing Hungarian groups since autumn 2006, many associations have been formed in Hungary since summer 2007 calling themselves the "national self-defence association".
"The common feature of these gatherings is that they define themselves as a civil organization when they publicly declare the preparation of their members for defence missions (disasters, national defence, defence of order), armed if necessary, moreover, by evoking the incapacity of the police, the army, in other words the state," they added.
They pointed out that everything was going according to the method which, based on the resentment of the political society and the parties, sought to disguise different political ambitions in a civilian way.
